[[File:Czesław Mystkowski Reclining nude.jpeg|thumb|''Reclining nude'' by [[Czesław Mystkowski]]]] '''Museum Pasifika''' (''Nusa Dua Bali'') is an [[art museum]] in [[Bali]], [[Indonesia]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Mann|first=Richard|title=Treasures of Bali, A Guide to Museums in Bali|year=2006|publisher=Gateway Books International|isbn=979-99853-4-X|pages=192}}</ref> It presents the [[Asia]]n [[Pacific Ocean|Pacific]]’s variety of cultural artefacts. The museum was founded in 2006 by Moetaryanto P and Philippe Augier.{{citation needed|date=May 2011}}
The museum's collection includes more than 600 artworks by 200 artists from 25 countries. The museum has a number of galleries:{{citation needed|date=May 2011}}
*Room I: Indonesian Artists *Room II: Italian Artists in Indonesia *Room III: Dutch Artists in Indonesia *Room IV: French Artists in Indonesia *Room V: Indo-European Artists in Indonesia *Room VI: Temporary Exhibition *Room VII: Artists on Indochina Peninsula: Laos, Vietnam, and Cambodia *Room VIII: Artists on Polynesia and Tahiti *Room IX: Premier Art of Vanuatu and the Pacific Islands Paintings of Aloi Pilioko and Nicolai Michoutouchkine *Room X: Tapa of Oceania and Pacific *Room XI: Asia: Several artworks on Japan, China, Thailand, Malaysia, and Myanmar and the Philippines
